==English==
===Noun===
'''[[booze]] [[bus]]'''
# {{AU}} [[police|Police]] vehicle used for administering blood-alcohol tests (to drivers), generally a mid-size bus converted or fitted out for the purpose.  (Introduced in [[New South Wales]] from 17 December 1982.)
#: 1982: ''Police 'booze buses' gear up for the start of random breath tests.'' &mdash; [[w:Sydney Morning Herald|Sydney Morning Herald]], 2 December 1982, page 16.  Quoted in G. A. Wilkes, ''A Dictionary of Australian Colloquialisms'', second edition, 1985, [[w:Sydney University Press|Sydney University Press]], ISBN 0-424-00113-6.